ww.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-02-27/hakumei-and-mikochi-anime-english-dub-stars-brittney-karbowski-amanda-lee/.143980|title=Hakumei and Mikochi Anime's English Dub Stars Brittney Karbowski, Amanda Lee|website=Anime News Network|language=en|access-date=2019-05-30}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2019 ||''[[Nichijou]]''|| Mai Minakami ||  ||<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-05-28/nichijou-anime-english-dub-video-previews-brittany-lauda-as-mai/.147211|title=Nichijou Anime's English Dub Video Previews Brittany Lauda as Mai|website=Anime News Network|language=en|access-date=2019-05-30}}</ref>\n|-\n|TBA\n|''[[My Wife is the Student Council President]]''\n|[[My Wife is the Student Council President#Ui Wakana|Ui Wakana]]\n|\n|<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.animeherald.com/2016/03/27/brittany-lauda-plays-ui-wakana-wife-student-council-president-dub/|title=Brittany Lauda Plays Ui Wakana In My Wife Is The Student Council President Dub|author=|date=March 27, 2016|work=animeherald.com|accessdate=June 13, 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2019 ||''[[Fairy Tail]]''|| August (child) || ||\n|-\n| 2020 ||''[[Interspecies Reviewers]]''|| Maydry || ||<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/encyclopedia/people.php?id=124358|title=Anime News Network Brittany LAUDA|author=|date=January 11, 2020|work=animeherald.com|accessdate=February 4, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|}\n<!-- IN RESUME BUT NEEDS NOTABILITY\n| || ''[[Yu-Gi-Oh Arc V]]'' || Additional voices || Ep. 1 || resume\n| || ''[[Shomin Sample]]'' || Additional voices || Eps. 3-4 || resume\n| || ''[[Seraph of the End]]'' || Additional voices || Ep. 16 || resume\n--->\n<!-- NEED SOURCE\n* ''[[Fairy Tail]]'' - Michelia\n-->\n<!-- NEED NOTABILITY\n===Animation===\n* ''Double Rainboom'' - [[Pinkie Pie]], [[Scootaloo]]\n* ''Candy & Clyde'' - Candy || resume\n* ''Kassandra: Goddess of Awesome'' - Kassandra, Jenny || resume\n* ''Prince Adventures'' - Jesus Christ, Princess Jabari, Princess Subira || resume\n* ''Shattered Heaven'' - Catherine || resume\n* ''TOME: Terrain of Magical Expertise'' - Additional Voices || resume\n* ''The Life Givers'' - Young Life\n* ''Lora Vicious'' - Lora Vicious || resume\n===Live Action Dubbing===\n* ''[[NHK]] Original Series NextWorld'' - Mana, Young Mana, Young Mirai, Young Mom || resume\n-->\n\n===Video games===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\"\n|+ List of voice performances in video games\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\"| Notes\n! class=\"unsortable\"| Source<ref name=\"bio\"/><ref name=\"resume\"/>\n|-\n|2014\n|''[[Yandere Simulator]] ''\n|Osana Najimi\n|\n|Resume<!-- resume -->\n|-\n|2015\n|''[[HuniePop]]'' || Audrey Belrose || || Resume <!-- resume -->\n|-\n|2015\n|''[[Strife (2015 video game)|Strife]]'' || Blazer || || Resume <!-- resume -->\n|-\n|2016\n|''[[HunieCam Studio]]''|| Audrey Belrose, Brooke Belrose ||  || Resume<!-- resume -->\n|-\n|2017\n|''[[Battlerite]]'' || Pearl || || Resume <!-- resume -->\n|-\n|}\n\n<!-- NEED NOTABILITY\n* ''But I Love You'' - Leila (resume)\n* ''Block Slide Rush'' - Announcer (resume)\n* ''Lovely Little Thieves'' - Dawn (resume)\n* ''The Fantastic Fivesome'' - Mariah (resume)\n* ''Tokyo Hosto'' - Sakura, Office Lady (resume)\n* ''YIIK: A PostModern RPG'' - Crying Illuminati Pyramid, Mall Rats, others (resume)\n| || ''[[Rosenkreuzstilette]]'' series || Trauare Wrede || || resume\n--->\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|refs=\n<ref name=\"resume\">{{cite web|url=http://brittanylauda.com/wordpress/resume/|title=Resume \u2013 Brittany Lauda|author=|date=|work=brittanylauda.com|accessdate=June 13, 2016}}</ref>\n<!-- no check marks yet <ref name=\"btva\">{{cite web|url=http://www.behindthevoiceactors.com/Brittany-Lauda/|title=Brittany Lauda|author=|date=|work=behindthevoiceactors.com|accessdate=June 13, 2016}}</ref> --->\n}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Official website|http://brittanylauda.com/}}\n* {{AnimeCons name|id=5211}}\n* {{ann|people|124358}}\n* {{IMDb name|5204895}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Lauda, Brittany}}\n[[Category:1993 births]]\n[[Category:American voice actresses]]\n[[Category:American video game actresses]]\n[[Category:Casting directors]]\n[[Category:Voice directors]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:State University of New York at Geneseo alumni]]\n[[Category:People from Huntington, New York]]\n[[Category:21st-century American actresses]]\n[[Category:Actresses from New York (state)]]\n[[Category:People from Geneseo, New York]]\n[[Category:Actresses from New York City]]\n[[Category:Cosplayers]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use mdy dates|date=February 2019}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Brittany Lauda\n| image              = \n| other_names        = Bree Faith\n| birth_date         = {{Birth date and age|1993|02|18|mf=y}} <!-- posted on Facebook public profile -->\n| birth_place        = [[Huntington, New York]], U.S.\n| education          = [[State University of New York at Geneseo]]\n| residence          = [[New York City]], New York, U.S.\n| death_date         = \n| death_place        = \n| occupation         = Voice actress, ADR director and producer\n| years_active       = 2013\u2013present\n| spouse             = {{marriage|Matt Shipman|2018}}\n| URL                = http://www.brittanylauda.com\n}}\n\n'''Brittany Lauda''' (born February 18, 1993) is an American voice actress and voice director who has appeared in English language dubs of Japanese anime shows as well as video games.<ref name=\"facebook\">{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/BrittanyLaudaVO/info?tab=page_info|title=Brittany Lauda - Voice Actress|author=|date=|work=facebook.com|accessdate=June 13, 2016}}</ref> Her debut role was in ''[[Queen's Blade Rebellion]],'' where she voiced Mirim.<ref name=\"bio\">{{cite web|url=http://brittanylauda.com/wordpress/about-brittany/|title=About Brittany \u2013 Brittany Lauda|author=|date=|work=brittanylauda.com|accessdate=June 13, 2016}}</ref> \n\n== Biography ==\nLauda has been involved in many productions from [[Media Blasters]]. Some of her major roles are Plug Cryostat in ''[[Fight Ippatsu! J\u016bden-chan!!]]'', Audrey Belrose in ''[[HuniePop]]'', Cammot in ''[[Holy Knight]]'', Osana Najimi in ''[[Yandere Simulator]]'', and Ui Wakana the title character in ''[[My Wife is the Student Council President]]''. She and fellow voice director Melanie Ehrlich had a production company called MB VoiceWorks which worked on the dub for ''Holy Knight'' and casting for ''[[Ladies versus Butlers]].''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fandompost.com/2016/05/16/mb-voiceworks-closing-down/|title=MB VoiceWorks Closing Down|author=|date=May 16, 2016|work=fandompost.com|accessdate=August 9, 2016}}</ref>\n\nLauda graduated from [[Harborfields High School]] in [[Greenlawn, New York]], and the [[State University of New York at Geneseo]] with a Bachelor of Arts degree in history.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://root.evanced.info/harborfields/evanced/eventsignup.asp?ID=18024|title=Teen Advisory Board Meeting: Where are They Now?|website=root.evanced.info|access-date=2019-05-30}}</ref> She has also been an active [[Cosplay|cosplayer]] at anime and science fiction conventions under the name '''Bree Faith'''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.acparadise.com/acp/display.php?a=74366|title=Cosplayer Bree - ACParadise.com|author=|date=|work=acparadise.com|accessdate=June 13, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://patch.com/new-york/huntington/cosplay-sunday-presented-by-sparkboom|title=CosPlay Sunday (Presented by SPARKBOOM)|author=|date=|work=patch.com|accessdate=June 13, 2016}}</ref>\n\n== Personal life ==\nLauda married voice actor Matt Shipman in December 23, 2018.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/BrittanyLaudaVO/status/1076897651663257600|title=Since we are in NY for the holidays, our families wanted to celebrate Matt and I getting married (it\u2019s been over half a year lol). My cousin made this amazing cake, with custom toppers based on Nashira\u2019s drawing of Ichigo and Hiro!|last=Lauda|first=Brittany|date=December 23, 2018|website=@BrittanyLaudaVO|language=en|access-date=December 31, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n===Anime===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\"\n|+ List of dubbing performances in anime\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\"| Crew role, Notes\n! class=\"unsortable\"| Source<ref name=\"bio\"/><ref name=\"resume\"/>\n|-\n| {{dts|2013|09|24|format=y}} || ''[[Queen's Blade Rebellion]]'' || [[Queen's Blade Rebellion#Mirim|Mirim]] || debut role ||<ref name=\"ann 20150201\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2013-09-23/queen-blade/rebellion-english-dub-cast-confirmed|title=Queen's Blade: Rebellion's English Dub Cast Confirmed|author=|date=|work=animenewsnetwork.com|accessdate=June 13, 2016}}</ref><!-- resume -->\n|-\n| 2016 || ''[[Fight Ippatsu! J\u016bden-chan!!|Fight Ippatsu! Juden-chan!!]]'' || [[Fight Ippatsu! J\u016bden-chan!!#Plug Cryostat|Plug Cryostat]] || ADR Director || <ref name=\"mediablasterscastlist\">{{cite web | url = http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2015-07-22/media-blasters-casts-juden-chan-ladies-vs-butlers-english-dub-leads/.90787 | title = Media Blasters Casts Juden Chan, Ladies vs. Butlers! English Dub Leads | work=[[Anime News Network]] | date = July 22, 2015|accessdate=July 23, 2015}}</ref><!-- resume --><ref name=\"con profile\"/>\n|-\n| 2015 || ''[[Holy Knight]]'' || [[Holy Knight#Cammot|Cammot]] || dub producer, ADR Director ||<ref name=\"ann 20150201\">{{cite web|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2015-02-01/media-blasters-casts-brittany-lauda-devon-talbott-in-holy-knight-ova/.83848|title=Media Blasters Casts Brittany Lauda, Devon Talbott in Holy Knight OVA|author=|date=|work=animenewsnetwork.com|accessdate=June 13, 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"ann 20150123\">{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/press-release/2015-01-23/mb-voiceworks-to-produce-english-dubs-for-media-blasters/.83624|title=MB VoiceWorks To Produce English Dubs For Media Blasters |website=Anime New